    "notes": "The series has two distinct eras: 1) Original 1986-1990s classic recordings (episodes 1-68 with 40 short track parts), and 2) Modern 2025-2026 'Neue Abenteuer' re-recordings (episodes 1-4 so far with 22 tracks including intro/outro). I propose splitting the modern re-recordings into a separate series 'Hanni und Nanni: Neue Abenteuer' since they are a different product with different voice cast and production style. For the main series, I'm excluding the classic versions of episodes 1-4 as duplicates since the modern versions are being kept in the new split series. Episodes 5-68 remain as the classic versions in the main series, and episodes 69-80 are already modern productions that continue the series naturally.\nVerified all 4 Neue Abenteuer albums:\n- Folge 1 (4xrdTvOrQTFEGke8945KNt): Released 2025-10-30, 21 tracks, EUROPA/Sony Music label\n- Folge 2 (6zZk7LkH1m6YoWWm03YLiE): Released 2025-10-31, 22 tracks, EUROPA/Sony Music label\n- Folge 3 (2AtMEM0eThrrAFZgsVdI2t): Released 2025-12-05, 22 tracks, EUROPA/Sony Music label  \n- Folge 4 (6XTedYExfvjpVlgsqHg8Lh): Released 2026-02-13, 22 tracks, EUROPA/Sony Music label\n\nAll have modern chapter structure with Inhaltsangabe, Titelsong, Kapitel, and Outro tracks - completely different from the 1986 classic versions (40 short track parts, EUROPA Logo! label).\n\nClassic versions (01/, 02/, 03/, 04/) remain in the main series - these match the format of episodes 5-68 and represent the original 1986-1990s recordings that parents expect when browsing 'Hanni und Nanni'.\n\nAfter split, main series will have clean 1-80 episode sequence without duplicates.",
